  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nI need to connect to multiple postgres hosts with hibernate-reactive.\r\n\r\nWith the classic jdbc driver, we can define this property to connect to our HA postgres instance:\r\n\r\n`quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://my.host-1.com,my.host-2.com,my.host-3.com:5432/myDB`\r\n\r\nBut [here](https://github.com/eclipse-vertx/vertx-sql-client/blob/master/vertx-pg-client/src/main/java/io/vertx/pgclient/impl/PgConnectionUriParser.java#L42) I saw that the vert.x PgClient does not support multi host connections directly in connection URI.\r\n\r\nI created an issue in vertx-sql-client [here](https://github.com/eclipse-vertx/vertx-sql-client/issues/1250) and a developer said me that it would be already possible by using the PgConnectOptions and a PgPool.\r\n\r\nCan you support connection pool to multi hosts through your implementation ?",
